			<div class="content" id="post-content-4556472">
									

<p>Since the COVID-19 outbreak ‘got serious’(it was serious from the beginning) most people have begun spending <em>a lot</em> of time locked up in their houses or only going out to very small outdoor gatherings per the advice of health organizations. With the extra time being spent in homes, what have you been up to to keep yourself from going stir crazy? Any new hobbies taken up? New cooking recipes that you’d like to share? Advanced spring cleaning to brag about getting done?</p>
<p>To start things off, so far I’ve:<br />
- finally begun writing my skip ideas properly and working towards putting an article up.<br />
- been combing through the articles related to subjects of my interest in the SCP universe. It’s truly impressive to see the mass of work we’ve been able to build as a community here.<br />
- Taught myself 2 new recipes. Currently housing some excellent and extensive leftovers.<br />
- Started researching new artistic mediums (Watercolor and dip pen inking) for me to experiment with and practice while holed up flattening the curve.</p>

							</div>

								
